e mind of man, but if one truly wanted to know the mind of God, you must study physics.\n\n- Iain Banks, The Business\n|\nIt’s tough, but if you want to survive, sometimes you have to do the seemingly impossible.\n\n- Adele          Rose, Shattered\n|\nAs time and space are bent by gravity, so too is truth bent by power.\n\n- James\n|\nI thought about writing the character as male, but then I would be forced to portray him as a woman in a man's body.\n\n- Christopher\n|\nIn a world where the dead have returned to life, the word' trouble' loses much of its meaning.\n\n- Dennis\n|\nIntelligence is more important than strength, that is why earth is ruled by men and not by animals.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nOur love grows soft if it is not strengthened by truth, and our truth grows hard if it is not softened by love.\n\n- John\n|\nAnne laughed.'I don't want sunbursts or marble halls, I just want you.\n\n- L.M. Montgomery, Anne of the Island\n|\nA general cry of 'What book? What book? Let us see this famous book!\n\n- Diana Gabaldon, An Echo in the Bone\n|\nWhen life gives you lemons, use Cosmic Ordering!\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering Guide\n|\nWhen you have eliminated all which is impossible, then whatever remains, however improbable, must be the truth.\n\n- Arthur Conan Doyle, The Case-Book of Sherlock Holmes\n|\nOnly ,a lonely heart Can tell What it meansTo be lonely\n\n- Sami\n|\nNo matter what your history has been, your destiny is what you create today. What are you going to create?\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Life, the Truth, and Being Free\n|\nI suppose she's right. It's like a metaphor for life: No one wants an ornery old goat, but we can't resist opening the door ayway. We can't keep from hoping.\n\n- Lauren Myracle, Bliss\n|\nEducation is just KnowledgeYour attitude, Your Behavior Is not depends on YourEducation\n\n- M.Zuber\n|\nTime eventually positions most photographs, even the most amateurish, at the level of art.\n\n- Susan\n|\nThere are several grave consequences that come with lack of knowledge, the paramount is destruction.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nFive exclamation marks, the sure sign of an insane mind.\n\n- Terry Pratchett, Reaper Man\n|\n@bobbybaird i'm a writer, so are you. we try to compose our thoughts and words for effect as well as sense. vain of us? a bit.\n\n- Walter\n|\nyou wanted it all to make senseand you wanted the most complicated answer,but the answer is simple.just be.\n\n- AVA., you are safe here.\n|\nFor you to be able to be fruitful, to multiply and saturate the earth with your products, you have to first know how to properly use the currency of time.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nBeginnings are so important. Just finding that right moment to introduce this character, this world, it’s everything.\n\n- Aryn\n|\nOne, two, three, Im gon be crazy and free.\n\n- Nick\n|\nPeople are always complaining that life's not fair, but that simply isn't true. Life is extraordinarily fair. It's just not centered on you.\n\n- Lynn Marie Sager, A River Worth Riding\n|\nEverywhere I go, your beauty spills into my day. The trees were never this verdant. The birdsong never this sweet.\n\n- Kamand\n|\nKnowledge is a social construct, a consensus among the members of a community of knowledgeable peers.\n\n- Kenneth A. Bruffee, Collaborative Learning: Higher Education, Interdependence, and the Authority of Knowledge\n|\nIf the way of wisdom was easy, anyone would have walked in. Wisdom is not a whore she is a shy mademoiselle so only those who strives wins her heart.\n\n- Rajesh\n|\nGrandfather : Death is nothing to be afraid of.Renee : It's not death I'm afraid of.Grandfather: What is it, then?\n\n- Yvonne Wood, Dead Beautiful\n|\nWriting doesn’t get easier with experience. The more you know, the harder it is to write.\n\n- Tim\n|\nI wonder if I'll ever have to decide which is worse, life as we're living or no life at all.\n\n- Susan Beth Pfeffer, Life As We Knew It\n|\nYou do not win by struggling to the top of a caste system, you win by refusing to be trapped within one at all.\n\n- Naomi Wolf, The Beauty Myth\n|\nDon't look at me like that,' said Ruza.'Like what?''Like I'm a beautiful book you're about to open and plunder with your greedy mad eyes.\n\n- Laini Taylor, Strange the Dreamer\n|\nShe may not be like everyone else, but neither am I.\n\n- Jessica Marie Baumgartner, The Golden Rule\n|\nLady, I do not make up things. That is lies. Lies are not true. But the truth could be made up if yo know how. And that's the truth.\n\n- Lily\n|\nChange is automatic, but Growth is intentional.\n\n- Izey\n|\nIt isn't that I dislike artists, but I can't stand anyone who puts on those ponderous airs of a man of character.\n\n- Osamu Dazai, The Setting Sun\n|\nBe mindful of the link between action and outcome. Ask yourself: If I repeat today's action 365 times, will I be where I want to be in a year?\n\n- Guideposts\n|\nWhen you don't know where you're going, you drive on the highway.\n\n- Roger Hedden, Bodies, Rest and Motion.\n|\nProclaim your pride and bitterness loudly to the world, but to me speak softly, and tell me simply that she doesn't love you.\n\n- Edmond Rostand, Cyrano de Bergerac\n|\nWe must not think of the things we could do with, but only of the things that we can't do without.\n\n- Jerome K. Jerome, Three Men in a Boat\n|\nBeauty is not who you are on the outside, it is the wisdom and time you gave away to save another struggling soul like you.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nI thought about how mothers feed their babies with tiny little spoons and forks so I wondered, what do Chinese mothers use? Toothpicks?\n\n- George\n|\nYou know, it's hard work to write a book. I can't tell you how many times I really get going on an idea, then my quill breaks. Or I spill ink all over my writing tunic.\n\n- Ellen DeGeneres, The Funny Thing Is...\n|\nHe felt as he always did when he finished a book — queerly empty, let down, aware that for each little success he had paid a toll of absurdity.\n\n- Stephen King, Misery\n|\nIf you are filled with your own ways and bored with life, check your relationship with God - your boredom could be a signal that you have slide away from your creator.\n\n- ANIKOR\n|\nDeath is a stripping away of all that is not you. The secret of life is to 'die before you die' --- and find that there is no death.\n\n- Eckhart\n|\nOf all the wonders that I have heard,It seems to me most strange that men should fear;Seeing death, a necessary end,Will come when it will come.(Act II, Scene 2)\n\n- William Shakespeare, Julius Caesar\n|\nThere are people in the world so hungry, that God cannot appear to them except in the form of bread.\n\n- Mahatma\n|\nAll that tread,The globe are but a handful to the tribes,That slumber in its bosom.\n\n- William\n|\nI choose to believe God had a more direct involvement in the creation of my heart and consciousness than in the creation of any book, no matter how thick or old it may be.\n\n- P.S. Baber, Cassie Draws the Universe\n|\nno one needs love from youmore than you need love from you.love yourself first,and you will always be in love.\n\n- AVA., you are safe here.\n|\nEVERYONE NEED EDUCATION,ITS THE NEED OF A NATION,IN IT IS FUTURE'S FOUNDATION,IT LEADS TO HEARTS ASPIRATION,AND TOMORROWS INSPIRATION.\n\n- merlin8thomas\n|\nBefore you criticize a man, walk a mile in his shoes. That way, when you do criticize him, you'll be a mile away and have his shoes.\n\n- Steve\n|\nLife is a journey filled with experiences but without the experiences, there will be no life.\n\n- Kemi Sogunle, Beyond the Pain by Kemi Sogunle\n|\nJust move to the Internet, its great here. We get to live inside where the weather is always awesome.\n\n- John\n|\nThere are many, many types of books in the world, which makes good sense, because there are many, many types of people, and everybody wants to read something different.\n\n- Lemony Snicket, The Bad Beginning\n|\nRoutine ruins the life, variety vitalise the life.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nThey spoke of small things at first, since it was best, when reattaching threads, to begin with the easiest knots.\n\n- Chris Cleave, Everyone Brave is Forgiven\n|\nThe purpose of relationship is not to have another who might complete you, but to have another with whom you might share your completeness.\n\n- Neale\n|\nIf a woman laughs when you hurt her, you ought to cry, for you have lost her; if she cries, you may laugh, for you have a worthy soulmate.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nFor, let me tell you that the more the pleasures of the body fade away, the greater to me are the pleasure and charm of conversation.\n\n- Plato, Republic: Books 1-5\n|\nThere has always been, for me, this other world, this second world to fall back on--a more reliable world in so far as it does not hide that its premise is illusion.\n\n- Graham Swift, Ever After\n|\nNeatness, madam, has nothing to do with the truth. The truth is quite messy, like a wind blown room.\n\n- William\n|\nFeelings don't have logic, hence one must not question Why & How!\n\n- Ramana\n|\nWe weren't born to create excuses, we were born to create excellence.\n\n- Janna\n|\nNo matter what sort of car you are driving or how fast you drive, we all meet behind the same red light.\n\n- Moe\n|\nlove yourself,.,.,.,for the sake of  your better future\n\n- John Grisham, La tapadera\n|\nI never had one hour's happiness in her society, and yet my mind all round the four-and-twenty hours was harping on the happiness of having her with me unto death.\n\n- Charles Dickens, Great Expectations\n|\nReal Women are not Weak but are Wonderers, they Propel Men to Greatness\n\n- Samuel\n|\nI am afraid to show you who I really am, because if I show you who I really am, you might not like it--and that's all I got.\n\n- Sabrina Ward Harrison, Spilling Open: The Art of Becoming Yourself\n|\